Dialing to the T roaming customer center
How to turn Roaming auto dial on or off

[Roaming auto dial]is available while you are roaming. This feature simplifies the dialing process by automatically inserting international call code and Korean country code (82) before a number you entered manually or selected from the phonebook or call log

"You can make calls just as you would in Korea. Enter a number manually or select a number from the phonebook or call log and then select Call Korea. Example: To call 010-1234-5678 from Beijing to Korea, enter 010-1234-5678 (or select the number from phonebook or call log) and then select Call Korea"

"To call within a foreign country: Enter a number manually or select a number from the phonebook or call log and then select Call other countries. Example: To call a Beijing number while in Beijing, enter the number and then select Call other countries. To call another country while outside Korea: Enter the international call code, country code, and the number, and then select Call other countries. You can insert the international call code with a plus sign (press the 0 key) and must remove the first zero from the number. Example: To call 06-1234-5678 from Beijing, China to Osaka, Japan, enter +81-6-1234-5678, and then select Call other countries"
"If you have more questions, please contact the T roaming customer center. Enter 114 with the keypad and select Call Korea to contact the T roaming customer center (+82-2-6343-9000)"
How to turn Roaming auto dial on or off
"You can turn Roaming auto dial on or off. Select T roaming > Roaming auto dial and then select an option: On: turns on Roaming auto dial Off: turns off Roaming auto dial"

"The Sprint Connections Optimizer helps you manage and enhance your data experience by finding and connecting to the Sprint 4G Network and \"remembered\" Wi-Fi networks on your device. Active Wi-Fi connections may offer improved performance and generally improve battery life while allowing you to talk on the phone and use data at the same time. The Sprint Connections Optimizer works by searching for available \"remembered\" Wi-Fi networks and the Sprint 4G Network. If you do not leave your 4G or Wi-Fi antennas on all the time, you will only notice the Sprint Connections Optimizer operating at certain times of the day in a small number of locations on the Sprint network. Your 4G or Wi-Fi antennas will conserve battery by scanning for connections periodically (not continuously), and if no connection is achieved, the antennas will be turned off. You may also manually turn the antennas off during the scan period. To facilitate quality assurance and enable feature enhancements, information is collected about your battery levels, Wi-Fi and Sprint Network connections and usage. No personal information is collected.
To disable the Sprint Connections Optimizer, simply uncheck the box above."

"To enhance your data experience the Sprint Connections Optimizer will automatically connect you to Wi-Fi networks on your devices remembered list (e.g., your home network) and the Sprint 4G Network. Sprint has provided, through a recent maintenance release, the Sprint Connections Optimizer setting to help manage your Wi-Fi and 4G connections. To facilitate quality assurance and enable feature enhancements, battery level, Wi-Fi and Sprint Network usage information will be collected. For more information or to turn off Sprint Connections Optimizer, click \"More Information/Settings.\"
By clicking the \"I Agree\" button, you agree that your use of Sprint Connections Optimizer is governed by Sprints General Terms and Conditions of Service, which are available at http://www.sprintpcs.com/common/popups/popLegalTermsPrivacy.html."
